title: Grateful Dead Live at Warfield Theatre on 1980-10-06
lineage: Tracked with Audacity-> flac level 8 and checksums with TLH-> tags with Mp3tag
description:
Set 1

October 4, 1980, acoustic set:
Deep Elem
The Race Is On
It Must Have Been The Roses
Monkey And The Engineer
Rosalie McFall
Dark Hollow
To Lay Me Down
Oh Babe It Ain't No Lie
Ripple

October 6, 1980, acoustic set:
Dire Wolf
Cassidy
Jack-A-Roe
Monkey And The Engineer
I've Been All Around This World
Heaven Help The Fool
China Doll
On The Road Again
Bird Song
Ripple

October 9, 1980, acoustic set:
Dire Wolf
Dark Hollow
I've Been All Around This World
Cassidy
China Doll
On The Road Again
Bird Song
The Race Is On
Oh Babe It Ain't No Lie
Ripple

Set 2

October 4, 1980, early electric set:
Alabama Getaway
Greatest Story Ever Told
Candyman
Mama Tried
Mexicali Blues

October 6, 1980, early electric set:
China Cat Sunflower
I Know You Rider
Minglewood Blues

Selections from October Fourth, Sixth and Ninth, 1980
San Francisco, California
Warfield Theatre
First electric SBD source for 10/6 in digital circulation
